# Models & Serialization

## Action types

- Each action: struct in `internal/models/actions/`, `New*` constructor, `GetType()` string matching the YAML `type` key (lowercase, no spaces).
- Macro root is always a `loop`; tree mutations go through `AdvancedActionInterface` (`AddSubAction`, `SetSubActions`).
- Variable references use `${name}` strings; keep parsing/validation in `actions/`, not in serialize.

## Adding or changing an action

Update all of these in one change:

1. Action struct + `New*` in `internal/models/actions/`
2. `decode*` / `encode*` + `registerActionCodec` in `internal/models/serialize/action_codecs.go`
3. Round-trip test: build action → `ActionToMap` → `CreateActionFromMap` → compare fields
4. At least one `DecodeMacroFromMap` or YAML fixture test if macro-level keys change

```go
// ✅ GOOD — register in action_codecs.go init()
registerActionCodec("wait", decodeWait, encodeWait)
```

## YAML shape

- Keys are lowercase (`globaldelay`, `subactions`, `hotkey_trigger`).
- Decode tolerates `[]any` from YAML and `[]string` from in-memory maps (see `targetsFromMap`, `stringSliceFromAny`).
- Prefer `DecodeMacroFromMap` in tests over writing temp `db.yaml` unless persistence is under test.

## Repositories

- Access entities via `MacroRepo()` / `ProgramRepo()`; call `ResetAllForTesting()` in tests before rebinding config.
- Entity CRUD tests live beside repositories (`*_test.go`, `integration_test.go`); keep decode/encode tests in `serialize/`.
